channel.title: Vps problem! please help!
channel.description: Alright so I paid 20$ for my vps.. at vpsland.com.. after about 18 hours they emailed me the ip to connect with so i followed the http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,429240.msg3151495.html#msg3151495 ultimate vps guide.. went to run and all that i typed in the ip and it worked.. for a while.. later on i downloaded an ip changer thing and then it wouldn't work.. so i uninstalled that and it worked again.. and i was on my server and all and after like 10 minutes it just logged it off again i was like wtf and it wouldn't let me connect.. i did a full system restore and it still won't work!!! if worst comes to worst i'm going to call vpsland and ask them if they can do anything.. but i was hoping someone could help me on here.. if you do i will rep++:D here is what it says when i try to connect to the ip.. [code]Remote desktop can't connect for one of the following reasons: 1) remote access to the server is not enabled 2) the remote computer is turned off 3) The remote computer is not available on the network Make sure the remote computer is turned on and connected to the network and that remote access is enabled[/code] <-- i typed that myself bcuz it wouldn't let me copy and paste.. please help!!
